lead_paragraph: LEAD: A mild earthquake was felt in Southern California Saturday night but there were no immediate reports of injury or property damage, the authorities said. The quake came at 11:07 P.M. and measured 3.7 on the Richter scale of ground motion and released energy, said Robert O'Rourke, a spokesman for the California Institute of Technology in Pasadena.
